BILL NO. 1410 By: Jech and Pederson of the
2 Senate
3 and
4 Patzkowsky of the House
5
6 An Act relating to agriculture; requiring operation
of an Ag in the Classroom Education Program within
7 the Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and
Forestry; providing for development of curriculum for
8 K-12 programs in rural and urban schools; providing
for cooperation with certain agencies for operation
9 of program; authorizing the Oklahoma Department of
Agriculture, Food, and Forestry to provide
10 incentives; providing for funding sources; providing
for codification; and providing an effective date.
11
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5-13.1 of Title 2, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. The Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry
19 shall operate an Ag in the Classroom Education Program for the
20 purpose of educating students about agriculture within this state.
21 B. The Ag in the Classroom Education Program shall:
22 1. Develop curriculum for students in grades kindergarten
23 through twelve for Ag in the Classroom programs in urban and rural
24 schools;
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1410 Page 1

1 2. Provide training and workshops for teachers who utilize Ag
2 in the Classroom curriculum;
3 3. Utilize existing Department resources and related programs;
4 and
5 4. Cooperate with the State Department of Education and the
6 Oklahoma State University Oklahoma Cooperative Extension Service as
7 needed in development and operation of the program; provided,
8 however, the Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry
9 shall have sole authority over the program.
10 C. The Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry
11 may provide incentives if funds are available to teachers who
12 participate in the Ag in the Classroom Education Program and utilize
13 curriculum provided by the program. Teachers who complete
14 eligibility requirements for the incentives as promulgated by rules
15 of the State Board of Agriculture may receive incentives. The
16 incentives may include but not be limited to:
17 1. Teacher recognition in newsletters, the Ag in the Classroom
18 website, social media, or other methods of recognition for
19 completing eligibility requirements;
20 2. A monetary award to be used for agriculture-related class
21 projects or field trips;
22 3. Entering a teacher into a drawing for Ag in the Classroom
23 resources or other items; and
24 4. Awarding a teacher an Ag in the Classroom certificate.
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1410 Page 2

1 D. The Department shall directly receive all funds provided for
2 the Ag in the Classroom Education Program pursuant to Section 1104.3
3 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes. The Department may apply for,
4 accept, and use any gift, grant, or bequest from any source for the
5 purpose of discharging its duties.
6 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
7 Passed the Senate the 26th day of March, 2026.
